[Claude]: I found a significant new vulnerability! In `createUnixGitSSH` (line 2056) and `createWindowsGitSSH` (line 2044), the `user` (from `url.getUser()`) is written directly into a shell script without any sanitization. If the URL's user portion contains shell metacharacters, it leads to OS command injection when the shell script is executed by git.

The shell script is:
```sh
ssh -i "/path/to/key" -l "<user>" -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no "$@"
```

If `user` = `foo" -o ProxyCommand=touch${IFS}/tmp/pwned #`, the shell script would execute arbitrary commands.

